MASTERFLOW AI PROTOTYPE SPECIFICATION

PURPOSE

MasterFlow converts a natural-language employee request into a structured request that:

- Routes to the correct queue
- Preserves existing SLAs, approvals, and governance
- Collects enough information for the receiving team to begin work
- Asks only for information that is missing
- Generates a clear receiver-ready summary


PROTOTYPE SCOPE

The prototype will support:

- Intent detection
- Template selection
- Field extraction
- Diagnostic questions
- Work-readiness progress
- Business-impact recommendations
- Receiver-ready summaries
- Existing routing and priority rules
- Shipping-stopped P1 bypass

The prototype will not include:

- Live ServiceNow integration
- Production databases
- Authentication
- ERP or Outlook integration
- Production AI API dependency
- Carrier APIs


ROUTING READINESS

Routing readiness answers:

Does MasterFlow know where the request should go?

A request is routing-ready when:

- A template has been selected
- A destination queue is known
- Required routing information is collected
- SLA and approval rules are known


WORK READINESS

Work readiness answers:

Does the receiving team have enough information to begin working?

A request is work-ready when:

- Required diagnostic questions have been answered
- Safety or containment information has been collected when applicable
- The receiving team can understand what is happening
- A receiver-ready summary can be generated


CURRENT DIAGNOSTIC COVERAGE

Printer Ink:
- Supply status
- Printing impact

Help Desk / Printer Connectivity:
- Exact symptom
- Affected scope

Equipment Out of Service:
- Failure mode
- Safety or containment status

Warehouse Corrective Action:
- Problem category
- Immediate containment

Stock Check:
- Exact result needed

Systems Intake:
- Expected outcome
- Affected scope

HVAC:
- Affected area
- Safety concern

General Triage:
- Requested outcome
- Affected scope


CONVERSATION RULES

MasterFlow should:

- Ask one question at a time
- Ask no more than two important diagnostic questions when possible
- Never ask for information already provided
- Allow the requester to answer “Not sure”
- Explain why an important question is being asked
- Ask routing questions before diagnostic questions
- Never delay a Shipping Is Stopped P1 request
- Never ask an employee to perform unsafe repairs


RECEIVER BRIEF

Every completed request should provide:

- Request title
- Requested outcome
- Observed situation
- Expected situation when applicable
- Affected scope
- Key identifiers
- Business impact
- Actions already taken
- Safety or containment status
- Missing information
- Suggested first action

The suggested first action is a recommendation, not a confirmed diagnosis.


IMPLEMENTATION ORDER

Pass 1:
Diagnostic profiles in templates.js — COMPLETE

Pass 2:
Update request-engine.js to:
- Extract diagnostic answers
- Ask diagnostic questions
- Calculate work readiness
- Generate the Receiver Brief

Pass 3:
Update home.js to:
- Show work-readiness progress
- Show diagnostic information
- Explain why questions are being asked

Pass 4:
Update smart-request.js to:
- Display the Receiver Brief
- Display diagnostic answers
- Allow corrections